Program: Discovery
Title: Down Under - the geology of Australia
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwv9
Last Broadcast Date: 17 March 1997
The ancient landscape of Australia. Geologists have been conducting a scan of Australia, monitoring the ground beneath the continent, which until recently has remained a mystery. Using seismic technology more is also being found about some of the coast line including its coral reefs.